The paper focuses on generating videos using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also uses a recurrent attention mechanism, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and can be considered as an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses datasets related to motion and action recognition (KTH and UCF-101), which fall under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
